C TC20
(* JMM causality test case 20 (Pugh 2004). Load-buffering with BOTH a control and a    *)
(* data dependency on P0 (store x=r+1 guarded by a branch on the load) and a data dep   *)
(* on P1. The store value and its occurrence both depend on the load, so the cyclic     *)
(* outcome is thin-air. JMM DECISION: FORBIDDEN. Guard written r0==1 (the nonzero       *)
(* value) to model the source's if(r1!=0).                                             *)
{ }
P0(int *x, int *y) { r0 = READ_ONCE(*y); if (r0 == 1) ; WRITE_ONCE(*x, r0 + 1); }
P1(int *x, int *y) { r0 = READ_ONCE(*x); WRITE_ONCE(*y, r0 + 1); }
exists (0:r0=1 /\ 1:r0=1)
